publish:property.name: Description
publish:property.publish:value: A ProductOrder represents a request used to procure, update or remove one or many Products in the context of a ProductOffering through all its ProductOrderItems....

ownedComment.body:
A ProductOrder represents a request used to procure, update or remove one or many Products in the context of a ProductOffering through all its ProductOrderItems. <Note> Note that ProductSpecifications / Products covers 2 cases: 1) ProductSpecifications / Products bought by a Customer to the Service Provider, 2) ProductSpecifications / Products bought by the Service Provider to Business Partners.</Note> ProductOrder is a sub-class of RootEntity and therefore inherits from all its attributes and relationships. At least one CommunicationInteraction is the source of a ProductOrder. Then, additional interactions might happen such as the Customer asking why his order isn’t yet delivered or the Service Provider informing the Customer his order is completed. A ProductOrder might refer to an Agreement specifying all what has been approved by the PartyRoles involved in the ProductOrder. A ProductOrder and ProductOrderItems might be further described by Attachments. A ProductOrderItem may need other ProductOrderItems to be completed; this dependency is represented through the ProductOrderItemRelationship.
ProductOrder / ProductOrderItem are sub-classed as • BusinessPartnerProductOrder used to procure, update or remove Products for the Service Provider • CustomerProductOrder used to procure, update or remove Products for Customers

ownedComment.body: One or many PartyRoles might be involved in a ProductOrder / ProductOrderItem such as Distributor, Holder, Buyer or Product User. A ProductOrder and ProductOrderItems might be further described by Attachments. Each ProductOrderItem requires an action (AllowedProductAction) on a ProductSpecification or a ProductOffering. An AllowedProductAction is either an action n ProductSpecification or exclusively on a ProductOffering. The configuration required is described by the related Product even if it isn’t delivered yet. The prices applicable are related to the Product (ProductPrice) or to ProductOrderItem / PorductOrder when it corresponds to prices not specific to a Product such as a global of 5% on ProductOrder one-time fees. A ProductOrderItem may contain ProductOrderItems according to ProductOffering (BundledProductOffering / SimpleProductOffering) and ProductSpecification (Composite / Atomic ProductSpecification) structure. To deliver the corresponding Product, Place(s) to deliver and Appointment(s) might be needed. An Appointment is an arrangement to do something or meet someone at a particular time and location. A ProductOrderItem may also specify the commitment chosen (i.e. CommitmentTermOrCondition).
